INSERT INTO `trh_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2014-05-16 17:20:37','2014-05-16 17:20:37','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2014-05-16 17:20:37','2014-05-16 17:20:37','',0,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2014-05-16 17:20:37','2014-05-16 17:20:37','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','open','','sample-page','','','2014-05-16 19:27:19','2014-05-16 19:27:19','',0,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2014-05-16 19:27:19','2014-05-16 19:27:19','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 19:27:19','2014-05-16 19:27:19','',2,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(5,1,'2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','<p>We believe that school is a place for teaching and learning, where students feel safe, secure and supported. To provide this supportive learning environment, school communities must foster respect among all members of the school community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our school code of conduct is based on the belief that there are values fundamental to the well being of both the individual and society and that we are all responsible for the choices we make. It encourages students to recognize, respect diversity and individual differences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the process, we want students to develop self-discipline, self-respect which can be considered as the core of any person\'s growth.  We expect our students to maintain high standards of personal conduct that includes honesty, discipline, integrity, respect,  personal & social ethics and values.</p>','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2014-05-17 11:50:25','2014-05-17 11:50:25','',0,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=5',0,'page','',0),(6,1,'2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','About Us','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','',5,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2014-05-17 11:33:49','2014-05-17 11:33:49','<p>We believe that school is a place for teaching and learning, where students feel safe, secure and supported. To provide this supportive learning environment, school communities must foster respect among all members of the school community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our school code of conduct is based on the belief that there are values fundamental to the well being of both the individual and society and that we are all responsible for the choices we make. It encourages students to recognize, respect diversity and individual differences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the process, we want students to develop self-discipline, self-respect which can be considered as the core of any person\'s growth.  We expect our students to maintain high standards of personal conduct that includes honesty, discipline, integrity, respect,  personal & social ethics and values.</p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2014-05-17 11:33:49','2014-05-17 11:33:49','',5,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','<blockquote>\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\"\r\n\r\n<small>Jer 29/11-14</small></blockquote>\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year.\r\n\r\nThe goal of our institute, \"Knowledge for Service, especially the marginalized and poor and especially the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom\" resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, \"The mark of an educated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it\". It is our endeavor to instill in today’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.\r\n\r\nThe current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of reflective thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young mind to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our various activities such as sports, literary works, talents day, club activity, fun fair, computer education, Smart class, school awards many other related activities which rejuvenate inner energy of the student to have potential and genuine personality growth. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.\" Aristotle\r\n\r\nI place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and caliber?”Her encouraging thought is \" Be faithful over little things\".\r\n<h2 class=\"well alert alert-success\" align=\"center\">May God bless us all.</h2>','Principal Message','','publish','open','open','','principal-message','','','2014-05-18 10:43:22','2014-05-18 10:43:22','',5,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\" Jer 29/11-14\r\n\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year.\r\n\r\nThe goal of our institute, \"Knowledge for Service, especially the marginalized and poor and especially the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom\" resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, \"The mark of an educated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it\". It is our endeavor to instill in today’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.\r\n\r\nThe current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of reflective thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young mind to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our various activities such as sports, literary works, talents day, club activity, fun fair, computer education, Smart class, school awards many other related activities which rejuvenate inner energy of the student to have potential and genuine personality growth. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.\" Aristotle\r\n\r\nI place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and caliber?”Her encouraging thought is \" Be faithful over little things\".\r\nMay God bless us all.','Principal Message','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','',8,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','','Academics','','publish','open','open','','academics','','','2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','',0,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=10',0,'page','',0),(11,1,'2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','','Academics','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','',10,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','<ol>\r\n	<li>The school is open to all girls without any distinction of race, caste, creed and social status.</li>\r\n	<li>The school follows the syllabus prescribed by the Karnataka State Education Board. The medium of instruction is English and Kannada.</li>\r\n	<li>Students are admitted to standard VIII only.</li>\r\n	<li>Most of the students admitted are those who have successfully passed out from 7<sup>th</sup> Std of St.Teresa’s Higher Primary school.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who are coming from other schools have to clear an entrance test in Mathematics, Science, and English.</li>\r\n	<li>A pupil who has attended any unrecognized school cannot be admitted without a school leaving certificate (T.C) of the school previously attended, duely counter signed by the BEO of that range.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents seeking admission for their children should apply in writing in the prescribed application and pay the fees and agree to abide by the rules and regulations of the school.</li>\r\n	<li>Fees, once paid at the time of admission, are not refundable in any case.</li>\r\n	<li>The management has the last word in all matters relating to admission.</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary documents such as Birth certificate, Caste certificate, Income certificate, Bank A/C etc, must be submitted in photo copies, self attested by the parents.</li>\r\n	<li>True and complete information is to be furnished in the application. In case of any discrepancy, the management holds the right to cancel the admission of the child.</li>\r\n</ol>','Admission','','publish','open','open','','admission','','','2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','',10,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(13,1,'2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','<ol>\r\n	<li>The school is open to all girls without any distinction of race, caste, creed and social status.</li>\r\n	<li>The school follows the syllabus prescribed by the Karnataka State Education Board. The medium of instruction is English and Kannada.</li>\r\n	<li>Students are admitted to standard VIII only.</li>\r\n	<li>Most of the students admitted are those who have successfully passed out from 7<sup>th</sup> Std of St.Teresa’s Higher Primary school.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who are coming from other schools have to clear an entrance test in Mathematics, Science, and English.</li>\r\n	<li>A pupil who has attended any unrecognized school cannot be admitted without a school leaving certificate (T.C) of the school previously attended, duely counter signed by the BEO of that range.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents seeking admission for their children should apply in writing in the prescribed application and pay the fees and agree to abide by the rules and regulations of the school.</li>\r\n	<li>Fees, once paid at the time of admission, are not refundable in any case.</li>\r\n	<li>The management has the last word in all matters relating to admission.</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary documents such as Birth certificate, Caste certificate, Income certificate, Bank A/C etc, must be submitted in photo copies, self attested by the parents.</li>\r\n	<li>True and complete information is to be furnished in the application. In case of any discrepancy, the management holds the right to cancel the admission of the child.</li>\r\n</ol>','Admission','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','',12,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2014-05-18 06:28:30','2014-05-18 06:28:30','<strong>School Motto:-</strong> Knowledge for Service\r\n<h3>Our Vision for Education As Salesian Missionaries of Mary Immaculate (SMMI)</h3>\r\nCalled to live in God’s presence and share in Christ’s mission to transform the world into Love. Like Mary we, the SMMI sisters respond to God’s call in the footsteps of Christ, the teacher par excellence, sharing the vision of our founders Fr. Henri Chaumont. We are called to be imbued with a daring zeal to give the less fortunate a sense of hope, so that there is a better tomorrow for them.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We strive to develop the potential of our students by fostering in them human, moral, social and spiritual values.</li>\r\n	<li>We enable them to foster our spiritual heritage and help them to respond to life’s challenges with hope, courage and perseverance and a deep faith in God.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage them to be rooted in prayer and motivate them to commit themselves to serve the society and world at large.</li>\r\n	<li>We work for formation of right values for a better choice and decision making in our students.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage the students to be enriched by their own cultural heritage to dedicate themselves to people of every race, culture, language and nationality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpecial thrust of our educational effort is an active concern to make our students authentic and responsible citizens, to build a just and humane society.','Vision and Mission','','publish','open','open','','vision-and-mission','','','2014-05-18 06:30:21','2014-05-18 06:30:21','',5,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=14',0,'page','',0),(15,1,'2014-05-18 06:28:30','2014-05-18 06:28:30','<strong>School Motto:-</strong> Knowledge for Service\r\n<h3>Our Vision for Education As Salesian Missionaries of Mary Immaculate (SMMI)</h3>\r\nCalled to live in God’s presence and share in Christ’s mission to transform the world into Love. Like Mary we, the SMMI sisters respond to God’s call in the footsteps of Christ, the teacher par excellence, sharing the vision of our founders Fr. Henri Chaumont. We are called to be imbued with a daring zeal to give the less fortunate a sense of hope, so that there is a better tomorrow for them.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We strive to develop the potential of our students by fostering in them human, moral, social and spiritual values.</li>\r\n	<li>We enable them to foster our spiritual heritage and help them to respond to life’s challenges with hope, courage and perseverance and a deep faith in God.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage them to be rooted in prayer and motivate them to commit themselves to serve the society and world at large.</li>\r\n	<li>We work for formation of right values for a better choice and decision making in our students.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage the students to be enriched by their own cultural heritage to dedicate themselves to people of every race, culture, language and nationality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpecial thrust of our educational effort is an active concern to make our students authentic and responsible citizens, to build a just and humane society.','Vision and Mission','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 06:28:30','2014-05-18 06:28:30','',14,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(16,1,'2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','','Students','','publish','open','open','','students','','','2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','',0,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),(17,1,'2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','','Students','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','',16,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//16-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(18,1,'2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','<h3>Achievements:</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are pleased to  announce that our school is tagged with ISRD High Commission London.  Some of our students have successfully  cleared the district, state and National level Auditions. Varshitha of VIII &lsquo;D&rsquo;  has been selected as the &quot;Top talent student&rdquo; from our institution.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>We are Glad that our  school has got Accreditation and will be one of the Global Delivery Center in  Bangalore, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medals and Awards</h3>\r\n  <p>Our students have  appeared for various examination like Chinthana   and Taramandal science examination Navodaya  Kannada Examination and All India General Knowledge examination. Neetu, of X  &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the central merit scholarship in the All India General knowledge  exam.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Rachana J. Shetty</strong> of  VIII &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the second prize in state level singing competition conducted  by the Department of Education.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students have  secured the first prize in folk song conducted by the Lion&rsquo;s Club.  Keerthana and Vinaya Varshini of our girl- guides  are ever prepared to stretch their helping hands in social activities of our  school.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Kum.Raksha</strong> of X &lsquo;A&rsquo; Shwetha.  V Pravalika, Thaniya, Priyanka and Ayesha of X &lsquo;C&rsquo; are all set to receive  Rajyapuraskar award from the Governor of Karnataka.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students got the  first prize in the district level mock parliament competition conducted by the  Department of Education. Kum.Shambavi of IX &lsquo;B&rsquo; was selected for the state  level Mock Parliament Competition.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The high school students were adjudged winners  in Throw ball, Volley ball and Shuttle Badminton competition at the Zonal level  sports.  They secured the first place in  Shot put and Discus Throw and the third place in Javelin throw at the Zonal  level.  At the Taluk level, they were  adjudged winners in Table tennis and Basket ball.  Our students participated in the district  level Table tennis Competition.</p>','Results and Achievements','','publish','open','open','','results-and-achievements','','','2014-05-18 09:22:58','2014-05-18 09:22:58','',16,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','<h3>Achievements:</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are pleased to  announce that our school is tagged with ISRD High Commission London.  Some of our students have successfully  cleared the district, state and National level Auditions. Varshitha of VIII &lsquo;D&rsquo;  has been selected as the &quot;Top talent student&rdquo; from our institution.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>We are Glad that our  school has got Accreditation and will be one of the Global Delivery Center in  Bangalore, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medals and Awards</h3>\r\n  <p>Our students have  appeared for various examination like Chinthana   and Taramandal science examination Navodaya  Kannada Examination and All India General Knowledge examination. Neetu, of X  &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the central merit scholarship in the All India General knowledge  exam.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Rachana J. Shetty</strong> of  VIII &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the second prize in state level singing competition conducted  by the Department of Education.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students have  secured the first prize in folk song conducted by the Lion&rsquo;s Club.  Keerthana and Vinaya Varshini of our girl- guides  are ever prepared to stretch their helping hands in social activities of our  school.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Kum.Raksha</strong> of X &lsquo;A&rsquo; Shwetha.  V Pravalika, Thaniya, Priyanka and Ayesha of X &lsquo;C&rsquo; are all set to receive  Rajyapuraskar award from the Governor of Karnataka.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students got the  first prize in the district level mock parliament competition conducted by the  Department of Education. Kum.Shambavi of IX &lsquo;B&rsquo; was selected for the state  level Mock Parliament Competition.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The high school students were adjudged winners  in Throw ball, Volley ball and Shuttle Badminton competition at the Zonal level  sports.  They secured the first place in  Shot put and Discus Throw and the third place in Javelin throw at the Zonal  level.  At the Taluk level, they were  adjudged winners in Table tennis and Basket ball.  Our students participated in the district  level Table tennis Competition.</p>','Results and Achievements','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','',18,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2014-05-18 10:29:12','2014-05-18 10:29:12','<blockquote>\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\" \r\n<small>Jer 29/11-14</small>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year.\r\n\r\nThe goal of our institute, \"Knowledge for Service, especially the marginalized and poor and especially the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom\" resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, \"The mark of an educated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it\". It is our endeavor to instill in today’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.\r\n\r\nThe current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of reflective thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young mind to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our various activities such as sports, literary works, talents day, club activity, fun fair, computer education, Smart class, school awards many other related activities which rejuvenate inner energy of the student to have potential and genuine personality growth. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.\" Aristotle\r\n\r\nI place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and caliber?”Her encouraging thought is \" Be faithful over little things\".\r\nMay God bless us all.','Principal Message','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 10:29:12','2014-05-18 10:29:12','',8,'http://teresa.yahwehsoft.in//8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2014-05-18 10:31:19','2014-05-18 10:31:19','<blockquote>\r\n  <p>\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\"</p>\r\n  <small>Jer 29/11-14</small> </blockquote>\r\n\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year.\r\n\r\nThe goal of our institute, \"Knowledge for Service, especially the marginalized and poor and especially the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom\" resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, \"The mark of an educated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it\". It is our endeavor to instill in today’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excel