should be introduced by the parent or the guardian who will be responsible for his / her conduct.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.48cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Students seeking admission must forward to the Headmistress an admission form duly filled in, and signed by the parent or the guardian, with transfer certificate and progress report from the school last attended.  Scheduled Caste and Scheduled Tribe students shall produce a certificate to that effect.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Parents and guardians shall make sure of the name and date of birth of children before they are recorded in the school register.  The name and date of birth once entered in the school register cannot be altered without the written permission of the Director of Public Instruction.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>PROMOTION SCHEME</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Promotion to a higher class depends upon:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Regularity in attendance. </span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Regularity and quality of day-to-day participation in the class.</span></span></span><strong style=\"color: #0000ff; font-family: Verdana, serif; font-size: small; text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"images/admission-2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"251\" height=\"205\" style=\"cursor: se-resize !important; float: right;\" /></strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Opinion of teachers. </span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Written work and projects assigned by the teachers. </span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A pupil must obtain 35% marks in every subject.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>CONDUCT AND DISCIPLINE</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Every student should carry with him/her the school diary.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Pupils must be in their respective classroom at least 15 minutes before the time fixed for the classes to commence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">All pupils are expected to be present for assembly during which they pray together.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The attendance roll is taken at the beginning of the two sessions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">No child is permitted to leave the School premises without the permission of the Headmistress which will be granted only at the specific written request of the parents.</span></span></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>MEETINGS THE TEACHERS</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Parents may meet individual teachers before or after class with previous appointment only.  They are requested not to disturb them during class hours.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm;\"><br /><br /></p>','',-2,0,0,14,'2011-01-01 00:00:01',63,'Joomla!','2014-01-17 09:36:42',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2011-01-01 00:00:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_readmore\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"page_title\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"layout\":\"\"}',12,0,3,'','',1,83,'',0,'*',''),(83,195,'Academics','academics','','<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong><img src=\"images/Academic-banner.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"79\" /></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Investiture Ceremony</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">The School Cabinet is formed in view of fostering the leadership qualities in the future citizens and to involve the students in the planning and the implementation of the school progamme. The investiture ceremony was held on 7.6.2013. Sr Lisia, the superior of Bethany Convent, Jayamahal passed the light to the students. 24 of the cabinet members with the lighted candles pronounced the oath. Sr Cynthia, the headmistress administered the oath to them.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>School Assembly</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Daily school assembly begins with the prayer and reading the scriptures. Through the reading of the newspaper the students are acquainted with the day-today affairs of the country and of the world. On Thursdays each class in turn enacts a core-value of BES which helps in the assimilation of the value. This facilitates in building up the self-confidence of the students, drawing out the best from them.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Transit of Venus Event</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Nation level orientation workshop on transit of Venus was jointly organized by Vigyan Prasar, New Delhi and M P Birla Institute for Fundamental Research which was attended by Mrs. Matilda Fernandes, Science teacher. Later she organized an orientation progrmme for teachers. And students of our school and the neighboring schools. It was a rare sight to watch the Transit of Venus which occurs once in 105 years. It was viewed with much excitement from the terrace of our school, by the staff and students including the students of primary school and surrounding schools.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Clubs</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Student are enrolled as members of one or the other clubs i.e science and math club, Eco and Health club, Hindi club, Seva Dal, History club and Bosco Kids. Each club functions under the supervision of the in-charge teachers.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Sports</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">District and state level ball badminton tournament: Eight of our student played at the district level and there of them namely Anjum Fathima, Kousalya and Bhavana R were selected to participate in the Divisional Level tournament in Shimoga District </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Our Students participated in the volley ball and throw ball matches conducted by the department of education at the taluk level and reached semi finals in both.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Saranya K took part in taluk and district level 3 kilometers walking race and secured 2nd and 3rd place respectively</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">At the school level, we take care to see the involvement of every individual in all the activities of the physical education such as yoga, rhythmic activities, athletics, games and inter-house matches.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Art and Craft</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Art and craft is given due importance. Students prepare artistic and decorative articles. Tailoring is taught. Drawing and painting is done by every child.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Celebration of National Festivals:</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Students are encouraged to celebrate our national festivals with zest and much preparation. Our national flag is hoisted on Independence Day and Republic Day followed by cultural programmers. Gandhi Jayanthi, children\'s Day and Teacher’s day are celebrated with a spirit of love and respect.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Other celebration</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">Environment day, intonation girl child day, Hindi day, school patroness\'s day, Christmas celebrations, Vivekananda Jayanthi, Martyr\'s day and women\'s day celebrated as mother\'s day.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Excursions:</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">46 students of std X along with four teachers went on an excursion of four days to Goa on Nov. 18th 2013. Students of std IX and VIII visited Mysore and Srirarngapatna along with the staff. The tour was educative and informative availing a good break from the normal schedule.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"color: #365f91;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><strong>Out-reach programmes</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\">We reached out and cared for the less privileged of our society by sharing our resources with them. Students collected Rs. 13,700 during the social service week which was observed from 15th - 22nd December 2012. We set out to Home of Hope located at Kothanur which houses the destitute both men, women and children from around Bangalore. We visited children\'s home for HIV/AIDS and entertained them with songs and dances. This was instrumental in cultivating compassionate love for the poor and the marginalized among our students.</span></span></p>','',-2,0,0,81,'2014-01-16 05:28:29',246,'','2014-01-17 09:35:25',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-16 05:28:29','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\"