":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',24,0,3,'','',1,27,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',1,'*',''),(78,186,'About Us','about','','<div class=\"green\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<p class=\"bluefill\" style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The towering structure of Gulabi School that magnificently stands today at the cross-road of <strong>Jayamahal Extension</strong> is a symbol of pride and achievement of the school community of Gulabi. The present glory is a story of the past endeavors of those who contributed towards it. Gulabi remembers them with respect and gratitude.</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> </span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\">\r\n<div class=\"quote-cloud\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 19.1875px; text-align: center;\">The Founder Servant of God <strong>FC Mascarenhas</strong></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br /> <img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"images/th 1.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"351\" height=\"263\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\">\r\n<p> <strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Mgr RFC Mascarenhas</strong></span></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">, </span></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">the ‘Servant of God’ and the founder of the Bethany Congregation foresaw that the presence of Bethany Sisters in the capital city of Karnataka State would facilitate transactions in the Education Department and with the Government Officials. He with Sr Precilla, the then Superior General visited his friend Archbishop Thomas Pothacamury in 1995, seeking a suitable site in the Archdiocese of Bangalore. Mean while they obtained the necessary permission from Rt Rev Raymond D’Mello, the Bishop of angalore to erect a religious house in Bangalore Archdiocese. Ten months before the Founder’s death, a house at Jayamahal Extension was rented by Sr MAcrina, the superior General that became the first Bethany house in Bangalore. It was blessed by Arcbhishop Thomas Pothacamury on 19.03.1960.</span></span></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt;\">The pioneers:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>                     <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On 18march 1960, the pioneers Sr Anysia, Sr Julitta accomplished by Mother Macrina arrived in Bangalore. Mr Gregory Mathias, the Finance Secretary to the Government of Karnataka and his wife Ms Y Mathias – the uncle and aunt of Sr Laeta and late Sr Getta were instrumental in finding a rented house and procuring a site for the school and the convent. The rented house was named ‘Villa Theresa’ after the popular name “Little Flower” – St Therease of the Child Jesus, the second patroness of Bethany Congregation and the School – “Gulabi” under the patronage of the same saint.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Initial Innings:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>      <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On 18march 1960, the pioneers Sr Anysia, Sr Julitta accomplished by Mother Macrina arrived in Bangalore. Mr Gregory Mathias, the Finance Secretary to the Government of Karnataka and his wife Ms Y Mathias – the uncle and aunt of Sr Laeta and late Sr Getta were instrumental in finding a rented house and procuring a site for the school and the convent. The rented house was named ‘Villa Theresa’ after the popular name “Little Flower” – St Therease of the Child Jesus, the second patroness of Bethany Congregation and the School – “Gulabi” under the patronage of the same saint. The Initial Innings: The Archbishop of Bangalore laid the foundation stone for the school on 15 April 1961. Twenty-one tiny tots seeking good educations were enrolled into the portals of Gulabi School on 22 May,1960. The first block of the building was blessed on 23.05.1962. The school was accorded Education Departmental Recognition in 1962. Classes were added year that reached standard VII in the year 1966. By 1963 over 400 students were enrolled and Sr Anysia, the first headmistress of Gulabi School organized its first Annual Day on 24 January 1963 in collaboration with her staff. On 31 January,1965the sisters vacated the renter house and occupied the part of the school building for their residence and continued to concentrate on education.            </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">From Trickle to a Torrent:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>   <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">In 1967, Sr Fides upgraded the Primary School into High School with standard VIII, and the classes were housed in the premises of the Archdiocesan Social Wing - ‘Workers’ center”. IN 1973 they were shifted back to the newly constructed second floor of the present school building, Sr. Agnella’s arrival on June 9th 1973 as the Headmistress of the fully established High School, gave a new thrust and the school started marching towards great heights. Through her vision, passion and dedication she left indelible mark in the hearts of students and teachers and carved a niche in Bethany. This great Stalwart and eminent educationalist will continue to shine in the annals of Gulabi.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Sr Agnella was very concerned about suitable residence for sisgers away from school premises. Sr Elizabeth who took over as the superior of the convent and paid attention to this and shouldered the task of putting up a convent, in spite of financial stress. A site was purchased on the Nandidurga road and on 3rd December 1997 the present Convent building was inaugurated with the name ‘Bethany Convent’. Presently, Sr Flossy the animator keeps the community lively with the co-operation of the sisters, young and old. The presence of sr Lucina, the senior most member is a blessing and boon to the community with her young and energetic spirit. Sr Ann Teresa, who was the secretary of BES at one time and who was also elected as the President of AINACS, involves herself actively in the field of education as a resource person at various levels.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Following the foot steps of the great teacher –Jesus and being convinced of the importance of His teachings, Gulabi School strives to instill in the students, the BES Vision and Core Values through various activites. Gulabi studet guided by their teachers keep themselves abreast of times by involving actively in different movements like Y.S.M, Science – Eco – Mathematics clubs, Sevadal and Bosco Kids and channelize their energy creatively. The Girl-guide unit has brought Laurels to the School at state and national levels. The socio-religious and national days are celebrated with due respect and festivity.</span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; background: #ffffff; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\">A seed is sown :</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; border: none; padding: 0cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> the 22nd of May in the year 1960, 21 tiny tots carrying little bags with lots of </span></span></span></span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">hopes and dreams entered the portals of Gulabi School, that was the curtain raiser. The School was named after Saint Therese of Lisieux also called Little Flower. She lived in France, in the 14th Century.<img src=\"images/videos/seed.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: right;\" /></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.13cm; margin-bottom: 0.13cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.5cm;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A Cloistered Nun who attained the height of sanctity, by way of spiritual childhood a way of trust and surrender to God. She related to God as a loving Father. A short life ..... a premature death at 24, but a fruitful endeavour to love and serve selflessly. Before breathing her last, she is believed to have said,</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.13cm; margin-bottom: 0.13cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; font-variant: normal; line-height: 0.5cm;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\">“<span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">My Mission – To make God loved begins after my death. I will spend my Heaven doing good on Earth.I will let fall a shower of Roses “. Her love for Jesus and a deeper passion for human kind is manifested in the School motto which reads ‘</span></span><span style=\"color: #0066cc;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><strong>BLOOM FORTH IN LOVE FOR LOVE’.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">A tiny seed of faith and hope planted in 1960 on very thin soil with 21 students on roll watered with relentless perseverance, determination and the fear of God has grown from strength to strength to the strength of 1798 students. These are undoubtedly the marvels, miracles and mercies of the Lord.</span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> </span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr title=\"Our Goal\" alt=\"goal\" class=\"system-pagebreak\" />\r\n<p class=\"core\" style=\"font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; line-height: 21px; color: #000066; margin: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; width: 590px; font-weight: bold;\">To promote the glory of God by the holiness of the members of our institute and the service of the Kingdom of God</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br style=\"color: #4c4c4c; font-family: verdana; font-size: medium; font-weight: bold;\" /><strong class=\"style5\" style=\"color: #ff6400; font-family: verdana; font-size: medium;\">   Our Goal</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<div class=\"core\" style=\"font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; line-height: 21px; color: #000066; margin: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; width: 590px; font-weight: bold;\">Education for fullness of life for all, especially the marginalized 