left; font-size: 16px;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: blue; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; float: left; font-size: 16px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Happy are those who find wisdom and those who get understanding; For wisdom’s income is better than silver and her revenue is better than gold. (Wis. 3:13-14)</span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">I begin by thanking God almighty who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year. </span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The goal of our institute, “Education for fullness of life for all, especially the marginalized and rural poor and the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom” resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, “The mark of aneducated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it”. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It is our endeavour to instill intoday’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of lateral thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our magazine Gulabi Showers. It includes </span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">articles relating to science and technology, women, environment, puzzles, art and poems by our students.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">I place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and calibre.</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"font-variant: normal; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\">May God bless us all.</span></span></span></strong></h1>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',-2,0,0,81,'2013-12-31 04:48:49',246,'','2014-01-17 05:00:49',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-12-31 04:48:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',39,0,1,'','',1,149,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(80,188,'Infrastructure','infrastructure','','<p class=\"greenfill\" style=\"color: blue;\">SCHOOL INFRASTRUCTURE</p>\r\n<p>The school consists of 2 floors. There are 40 classrooms in the school. The class rooms are spacious and have proper ventilation for conducive environment for learning.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span class=\"style5\">LABORATORIES :</span></strong> The school is well equipped with laboratories. Students can conduct their practical lessons with ease, under the guidance of a teacher with ample scope for individual learning and an auditorium, which can comfortably accommodate more than a thousand students.</p>\r\n<p>The school has an excellent<strong> library</strong> which is spacious enough. The library has an exhaustive collection of books.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Karate classe</strong>s are held for the children from Classes 3rd to 7th, with a well trained instructor.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span class=\"style5\">Music and Dance:</span> Opportunity to learn music and dance is available for use by interested students. They provide an outlet for students to relax and let out tension.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"style5\">Playground :</span> with a vast playground and well experienced physical education instructor children are given all the benefit of having a healthy mind in a healthy body.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"http://gulabischool.org/images/comp.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Computer Lab\" width=\"331\" height=\"247\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 15px;\" />Gulabi school matches the <strong>best infrastructure and facilities</strong> required for imparting quality education to the wards of the parents from Indian Community. The school has got a science lab equipped with latest apparatus. The school has set up a well furnished<strong> library, a huge auditorium, a LCD Projector</strong> and other facilities like installation of Aqua Guard for safe drinking water, etc., Subjects like Mathematics, Social Science, languages and General Science are made interesting and meaningful through the use of technology in class rooms. The Computer lab of the school is capable of providing latest technological support and one on one learning of computers and related technological skills. The school has got a modern two storied building. The Class Rooms are well lit, spacious and airy, providing a conducing environment for learning.</p>','',-2,0,0,81,'2013-12-31 04:51:32',246,'','2014-01-16 05:52:49',246,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-12-31 04:51:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',7,0,2,'','',1,64,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(81,193,'Founder','founder','','<p class=\"bluefill\" style=\"color: black; font-size: 25px; text-align: center; font-weight: bold;\">The Founder of the Congregation</p>\r\n<div class=\"quote-cloud\" style=\"width: 300px; margin-left: 130px;\">\r\n<p class=\"jm-typo-title\" style=\"font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;\"><strong>Servant of God</strong>  <strong><span style=\"color: blue;\">Raymond Francis Camillus Mascarenhas</span></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\">           <img src=\"images/th 1.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"319\" height=\"239\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 40px;\" /></p>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: black;\">\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Raymond was born on 23 January 1875 to</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">J</span></span></span></strong><strong><span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">oanna and Lazarus Mascarenhas</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of Mangalore, then residing at Shimoga.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Having completed his academic and priestly</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">training in Mangalore, he was</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">ordained priest on 4 March 1900.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">He rendered pastoral service at Kallianpur, </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Udyavar and Agrar.  At St Sebastian’s Bendur </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Monsignor was the founder parish priest from 1914 to 1931.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 180px;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A man with deep God experience, far sighted vision and deep intellectual insight and obsessed with the</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">idea of sharing God’s love especially with the poor, he read the signs of the times and founded the Congregation</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">of the Sisters of the Little Flower of Bethany in the year 1921 at Bendur to provide an opportunity to those who</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">desirous of answering the call of God to religious life and to cater to the pastoral care of the people and educational</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">needs of rural children, especially girls.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">He was a man of God, known to be a compassionate pastor, an eloquent speaker and powerful preacher,</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">an efficient administrator, an eminent educationist and a writer. Having served as the Vicar General of</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">the Diocese of Mangalore from 1931 to 1941 he continued to direct the Congregation that he founded.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">He dared to tread the unbeaten paths, where others dared not, while taking up new initiatives. In recognition</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of his valuable services the Holy Father, Pope Pius the XII conferred on him the title – Domestic Prelate.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 90px;\"> </p>\r\n</div>','',-2,0,0,14,'2014-01-13 19:02:04',246,'','2014-01-23 06:03:15',252,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-13 19:02:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',42,0,1,'','',1,73,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*','');
